Google's hardware division is facing layoffs and departure of Fitbit leaders, with the majority of impacts on the augmented reality division. Google spokesperson confirmed the layoffs but did not specifically confirm the departure of Fitbit leaders. Google remains committed to AR initiatives and serving Fitbit users.

- Google is laying off hundreds of hardware workers, particularly in its augmented reality division.
- Fitbit co-founders and other Fitbit leaders are leaving the company entirely.
- The layoffs are mainly affecting the 1P AR Hardware team.
- Google is still committed to other AR initiatives and AR experiences in its products.
- Fitbit will continue to be supported and will remain a key part of Google's new organizational model, focusing on health innovations and wearable devices.
- Impacted employees will have the opportunity to apply for open roles across Google.
- Google is providing support to impacted employees, including outplacement services and severance offerings.
